[32m+[m[32m**Choosing the right radius helper**[m
[32m+[m
[32m+[m[32m- Use `.rSafe` for most cards, containers, and components â€” it adapts gently without turning corners into circles.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Use `.r` when you need aggressive scaling (avatars, pills, circular buttons) so the radius grows with the element.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Use `.rFixed` when you need a hard pixel radius (badges, icon chips) that should never scale.[m
[32m+[m[32m- Need to tighten or loosen the clamp? Call `ScaleManager.instance.setRadiusSafeBounds(minMultiplier: 0.9, maxMultiplier: 1.2);`.[m
[32m+[m
